ing at \u2265 j that is > some threshold? This is complex.\n\nAlternative: for each segment i+1, precompute `min_from[j]` = min sum of segment i+1 starting at \u2265 j. Then segment i at position p is feasible if `min_from[p+len_i]` > ... wait, we need sum(i+1) > sum(i), so if min_from[p+len_i] > sum_i(p), it's feasible.\n\nSo: segment i at p is feasible if `min_achievable_sum[i+1][p+len_i] > sum_i(p)`.\n\nAnd `min_achievable_sum[i][j]` = min over feasible p\u2265j of sum_i(p).\n\nLet me implement this with binary search on k.",
